description:
**Job Overview**  
Premier Connecticut firm seeks attorney to assist on a part-time basis of 25 hours a week. The ideal candidate will have a strong background with diverse practice areas including:

* Probate court conservatorship hearings;
* Trust and probate litigations;
* Evidentiary hearings;
* Debt collection;
* Administrative appeals hearings;
* Personal injury suits;

The successful candidate will have the following experience:

* Solid knowledge of Connecticut civil practice and procedure;
* Solid research and analytical skills;
* Drafting motions, memos, discovery and pleadings;
* Strong organizational and high management skills;
* Must be admitted in Connecticut (New York admission a plus)

This is an excellent opportunity for someone looking for a team, friendly collaborative work environment.  
\\*

Job Type: Part-time

Pay: $60,000.00 - $65,000.00 per year

Expected hours: 25 per week

Schedule:

* Monday to Friday

Experience:

* Personal injury law: 2 years (Preferred)
* Legal counsel: 2 years (Required)

Ability to Commute:

* Norwalk, CT 06854 (Required)

Work Location: In person
